First Lady Jill Biden spoke at the White House's Roosevelt Room, highlighting the importance of supporting military families, particularly the National Guard. She shared personal stories of her father's service in World War II and her son Beau's deployment to Iraq. Biden emphasized the need to tell the stories of National Guard members and their families through the Joining Forces initiative. She acknowledged the sacrifices and resilience of military kids and expressed gratitude for their courage. Biden invited the children to share their experiences and discussed ways to further support them.